{"action": "add_entry", "entry": {"bookmarked": false, "feed": "http://twitter", "feed_image": "/twitter_profile_pics/shizhediao.jpg", "feed_title": "Twitter", "id": "http://twitter|2009481573217784016", "like_count": 464, "link": "https://x.com/shizhediao/status/2009481573217784016", "published": "2026-01-09T04:25:16.000Z", "reply_count": 18, "retweet_by": "@jm_alexia", "retweet_count": 78, "retweet_original_author": "@shizhediao", "retweet_original_avatar": "/twitter_profile_pics/shizhediao.jpg", "summary": "<div>RLVR is powerful \u2014 but how do you train with multiple rewards effectively? GDPO (not GRPO) is coming. \n\nWe introduce Group reward-Decoupled Normalization Policy Optimization (GDPO), a new multi-reward RL algorithm that consistently improves per-reward convergence over GRPO</div>\n<div><img src=\"/twitter_media/2009481573217784016_0.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;\"/></div>", "thumbnail": "", "title": "shizhediao", "viewed": false}}
{"action": "add_entry", "entry": {"bookmarked": false, "feed": "http://twitter", "feed_image": "/twitter_profile_pics/SakanaAILabs.jpg", "feed_title": "Twitter", "id": "http://twitter|2009295976746635364", "like_count": 442, "link": "https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/2009295976746635364", "published": "2026-01-08T16:07:46.000Z", "reply_count": 14, "retweet_by": "@jm_alexia", "retweet_count": 88, "retweet_original_author": "@SakanaAILabs", "retweet_original_avatar": "/twitter_profile_pics/SakanaAILabs.jpg", "summary": "<div>Introducing Digital Red Queen (DRQ): Adversarial Program Evolution in Core War with LLMs\n\nBlog: https:// sakana.ai/drq Core War is a programming game where self-replicating assembly programs, called warriors, compete for control of a virtual machine. In this dynamic</div>\n<div><img src=\"/twitter_media/2009295976746635364_0.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;\"/></div>", "thumbnail": "", "title": "SakanaAILabs", "viewed": false}}
{"action": "add_entry", "entry": {"bookmarked": false, "feed": "http://twitter", "feed_image": "/twitter_profile_pics/jackbot_cs.jpg", "feed_title": "Twitter", "id": "http://twitter|2009409486621167625", "like_count": 302, "link": "https://x.com/jackbot_cs/status/2009409486621167625", "published": "2026-01-08T23:38:49.000Z", "reply_count": 12, "retweet_by": "@jm_alexia", "retweet_count": 36, "retweet_original_author": "@jackbot_cs", "retweet_original_avatar": "/twitter_profile_pics/jackbot_cs.jpg", "summary": "<div>Today, we introduce WebGym, the largest-to-date open-source RL environment for web agent training that contains 300k tasks and a rollout framework optimized specifically for web environments&#x27; rollout speed. We reveal the effects of essential scaling directions we observe with</div>\n<div><img src=\"/twitter_media/2009409486621167625_0.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;\"/></div>", "thumbnail": "", "title": "jackbot_cs", "viewed": false}}
